{
  "texts": [
    "The framework of SPMM extends the structure of the dual-stream VLP models 27, 28, 39.",
    "Dual-stream VLP models encode the input for each modality with an unimodal encoder, then use another encoder module to perform cross-attention by using one modality feature as a query and the other modality feature as a key/ value.",
    "When a training molecule is given, SPMM takes the molecule's SMILES string and its property vector (PV) as multimodal data inputs as shown in Fig. 1a.",
    "The SMILES and PV are passed through their corresponding unimodal encoders, which perform self-attention where embedded inputs become the key, query, and value.",
    "After two unimodal features are obtained, contrastive learning aligns the SMILES and PV features into the same embedding space by assimilating the features that contain the same context."
  ]
}